'''Side-entrance Sarcophagus Chamber''' (横口式石槨) refers to a type of horizontal stone burial structure observed in the later to terminal phases of the Kofun period. It is also known as '''sekkanshiki Sekishitsu''' (石棺式石室).
This type of burial chamber is constructed using cut stones, designed to house {{ill|wooden coffins|ja|木棺|1=Wooden Coffin|qq=draft|qq=draft}} or {{ill|dry lacquer coffins|ja|乾漆棺|1=Kanshitsu coffin|qq=draft|qq=draft}}. The chamber features an opening on one of its shorter sides. In some cases, it includes an antechamber or {{ill|Endō|lt=passageway (sen-dō)|ja|羨道|1=endō|lt=endō (tomb entrance)|qq=draft|qq=draft}}.
The distribution of such burial structures is primarily concentrated in the {{ill|Kinai region|ja|畿内|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, with notable examples including the {{ill|Kannonzuka Kofun|ja|観音塚古墳|qq=draft|qq=draft}} in {{ill|Habikino, Osaka|ja|羽曳野市|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, and the {{ill|Takamatsuzuka Kofun|ja|高松塚古墳|qq=draft|qq=draft}} in {{ill|Asuka, Nara|ja|明日香村|qq=draft|qq=draft}}.
